reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and great looking L-desk
reviews.reviewText: I bought this on a flash sale on black Friday for a great price (139.00). I have to say it's worth it at that price point. The assembly wasn't hard, but it did take a few hours and I think either I swapped some screws or they gave me more of the long screws and not enough of the top screws. Either way, there was plenty of screws so unless something really terrible happens the table tops will not be leaving the desk of their own accord. There are instructions for having the long side on either the left or the right, and the whole thing is sturdy.The desk looks good. I'd say the only gripes are that the computer sits where my foot rest used to be so i keep almost kicking the computer during longer gaming sessions, and there's only 3 plugs on the little power strip that sits on top. I can't tell if it's a surge protector either. Since your computer sits underneath, you may have some issues reaching the power button (especially for me since my computer case has RGB and a window so i had to put it in with the power button in the rear corner of the desk). It may sound like I'm not enjoying the product, but i moved up from folding utility table desk to this one so I'm still pretty satisfied, besides if I had installed it with the left side longer orientation i wouldn't have the power button shoved into the corner.
